{{Infobox journal | title = Mycological Progress | cover = | editor = [[Franz Oberwinkler]] | discipline = [[Mycology]] | former_names = | abbreviation = Mycol. Prog. | publisher = [[Springer Science+Business Media]] | country = | frequency = Continuous | history = 2002–present | openaccess = [[Hybrid open access journal|Hybrid]] | license = | impact = 1.543 | impact-year = 2013 | website = https://www.springer.com/life+sciences/plant+sciences/journal/11557 | link1= https://link.springer.com/journal/volumesAndIssues/11557 | link1-name = Online access | JSTOR = | OCLC = 67618445 | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 1617-416X | eISSN = 1861-8952 }} '''''Mycological Progress''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[scientific journal]] covering the study of [[fungi]] including [[lichen]]s. It is published by [[Springer Science+Business Media]] on behalf of the [[German Mycological Society]]. Its [[editor in chief]] is [[Franz Oberwinkler]].<ref name="official">{{cite web |url=https://www.springer.com/life+sciences/plant+sciences/journal/11557 |title=Mycological Progress |publisher=[[Springer Science+Business Media]] |work=Mycological Progress |accessdate=17 Mar 2015}}</ref>
==History== The journal was established in February 2002 by the [[German Mycological Society]] under founding and current editor-in-chief, Franz Oberwinkler ([[University of Tübingen]]). Originally published by botanical publisher, [[IHW-Verlag]] ([[Eching, Freising|Eching]]), the title transferred to Springer in 2006 by which time it was the official journal of ten European national mycological societies.<ref name="official"/><ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1007/s11557-006-0503-z |title=Mycological Progress goes international |journal=Mycological Progress |volume=5 |pages=1 |year=2006 |last1=Oberwinkler |first1=Franz |last2=Agerer |first2=Reinhard}}</ref> It was published quarterly until 2015 when it converted to continuous publication online and production of the printed version ceased.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.springer.com/life+sciences/plant+sciences/journal/11557 |title=Immediate publication with Continuous Article Publishing as of 2015! |publisher=[[Springer Science+Business Media]] |work=Mycological Progress |accessdate=17 March 2015}}</ref>
==Abstracting and indexing== The journal is abstracted and indexed in:<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.springer.com/life+sciences/plant+sciences/journal/11557?detailsPage=aboutThis |title=About this journal |publisher=[[Springer Science+Business Media]] |work=Mycological Progress |accessdate=17 March 2015}}</ref> {{columns-list|colwidth=30em| *[[AGRICOLA]] *[[BIOSIS Previews]] *[[Scopus]] *[[Science Citation Index Expanded]] *[[CAB Abstracts]] *[[Current Contents]]/Agriculture, Biology & Environmental Sciences *[[Elsevier Biobase]] *[[EMBiology]] *[[The Zoological Record]] }} According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2013 [[impact factor]] of 1.543.<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2014 |chapter=Mycological Progress |title=2013 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.scijournal.org/impact-factor-of-MYCOL-PROG.shtml |title=Mycological Progress Impact Factor |publisher=International Scientific Institute |accessdate=17 March 2015}}</ref>
